SIMPLE: capitulum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capitulum
<hw>Ca*pit"u*lum</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*p⟦icr⟧t"⟦usl⟧*l⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <er>Capitula</er>
<pr>(k⟦adot⟧*p⟦icr⟧t"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a small
head.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thick head of flowers on a very short
axis, as a clover top, or a dandelion; a composite flower. A capitulum
may be either globular or flat.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A knoblike protuberance of any
part, esp. at the end of a bone or cartilage. <note>[See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Artiodactyla</er>.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capivi</ent>⟦br⟧
